  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Blaise Ag\u00fcera y Arcas's work, titled \"What Is Intelligence?\", has garnered significant academic attention, reflected in its 1,644 citations. This preprint has successfully undergone peer review and is published in a reputable journal, demonstrating its influence in the field.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The scholarly work titled \"What Is Intelligence?\" by Blaise Ag\u00fcera y Arcas stands out due to its substantial academic footprint as reflected by 1,644 citations. This high citation count indicates a strong reception and relevance among peers in the field, suggesting that the concepts discussed in the paper resonate deeply within ongoing scholarly conversations regarding intelligence.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Published as a peer-reviewed article, this work represents a notable achievement in academic discourse. The successful peer review signifies that the research not only meets specific scientific standards but also contributes meaningfully to understanding intelligence\u2014an area of enduring interest in various disciplines including psychology and cognitive science.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">While there is no documented community discourse or public engagement on platforms such as Wikipedia or Reddit, the academic citations highlight its impact within scholarly literature. The fact that it has been frequently cited reflects its potential to inspire further research and discussions in subsequent studies.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Overall, the significant citation growth of Ag\u00fcera y Arcas's work underlines its importance in academia. As a preprint that has successfully transitioned to peer-reviewed publication, it indicates an active engagement within the scholarly community, contributing to the evolution of theories and ideas surrounding intelligence.</p>",
